 MBOMBELA – The residents walked from Produkta Motors to the local ANC headquarters in Nel Street to handover a memorandum of demands. “We are protesting against the political unrest and a lack of services in Pienaar,” said bishop doctor Douglas Mnisi, convener of the Msogwaba Stakeholder Forum. READ ALSO: ANC deputy chief whip’s husband arrested for perjury “The ANC councillors should be held accountable by the ANC and we want to encourage them to call community meetings and speak to us to find out what issues arise in the community,” Mnisi said. Other demands on their list included having their schools completed and not to have other protesters burn their roads. READ ALSO: Acting premier is ANC’s choice to fill position full-time